# HTTP Network Package Guide

## Project Overview

This is a comprehensive HTTP network package written in Haskell that provides type-safe implementations of HTTP concepts including methods, status codes, headers, and more. The package is designed with a focus on performance and well-tested parsing and serialization according to the relevant IETF, W3C, or other specifications.

Implement a high-performance HTTP client and server.

The library is organized into several key components:

### 1. HTTP Methods (`Methods.hs`)
- Type-safe representation of HTTP methods (GET, POST, PUT, etc.)
- Support for standard and WebDAV methods
- Efficient interning for method names
- Case-insensitive comparison and hashing

### 2. HTTP Status Codes (`Status.hs`)
- Complete set of IANA-registered HTTP status codes
- Type-safe status code representation
- Efficient numeric encoding
- Comprehensive documentation with RFC references

### 3. HTTP Versions (`Versions.hs`)
- Support for HTTP/0.9 through HTTP/3.0
- Efficient version encoding
- Type-safe version comparison
- Version-specific constants

### 4. Header Field Names (`HeaderFieldName.hs`)
- Central registry of all IANA-registered HTTP header field names, as well as common non-standard headers.
- Provides type-safe constants for all standard headers
- Implements case-insensitive comparison and hashing
- Uses interning for efficient memory usage and comparisons
- Headers are categorized as:
  - Permanent
  - Provisional
  - Deprecated
  - Obsoleted

